description: This palstave is in very good condition. The cutting edge is worn at one end. There is a raised shield shaped area below the stop ridge which is well developed. Good smooth patina. File marks on face of implement below stop ridge. Edge has been hammered sharp.
publications: NLL. A very similar palstave found near Wraysholme Tower, near Allthwaite, Cartmel, Cumbria (Lanes) is illustrated in Trans. C. W. (O.S.) XVI 152-156 - it is so like it might be from the same mould. The present whereabouts of the Wraysholme Tower palstave is uncetain.  Mr. Newby Wilson's effects were sold after his death. Note: Wraysholme Tower axe now in Barrow-in-Furness Museum. See CW (NS) LXIII.281.
